<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Kiker's U-Pull-It — Web Component Kit (parts bin, not a page layout)</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Saira:ital,wght@0,600;0,700;0,800;1,700;1,800&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@500;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
/* ============================================================
   CANONICAL TOKENS — copy this :root block into every page.
   Source of truth: Kiker's Site Style Guide.
   ============================================================ */
:root{
  --red:#DC161F;--red-700:#B4101A;--red-800:#8C0C14;--red-wash:#FDEDEE;
  --amber:#F6A100;--amber-300:#FFC74D;--amber-600:#D98200;--amber-wash:#FFF4DC;
  --ink:#0B0611;--white:#FFFFFF;
  --bg:#F4F4F6;--surface-1:#FFFFFF;--surface-3:#EFEFF1;--blue-wash:#F0F4F8;
  --text:#0B0611;--text-2:#55555B;--text-3:#86868D;
  --line:#E5E5E8;--line-2:#D8D8DC;--line-strong:#BEBEC4;--steel-700:#72767B;
  --green:#1E9E57;--green-600:#178A4A;--green-700:#0F6E3B;--green-on-wash:#0F6E3B;--green-wash:#E4F5EC;--green-line:rgba(15,110,59,.22);
  --grad-ink:linear-gradient(160deg,#0B0611,#1A1719);--grad-red:linear-gradient(135deg,#DC161F,#8C0C14);--grad-chrome:linear-gradient(135deg,#E3E6E8,#9A9FA4 55%,#D7DBDE);
  --r-xs:2px;--r-sm:3px;--r-md:4px;--r-lg:6px;--r-pill:100px;
  --e1:0 1px 2px rgba(11,6,17,.08);--e2:0 8px 20px rgba(11,6,17,.10);--e3:0 20px 48px rgba(11,6,17,.16);--glow-red:0 0 0 1px rgba(220,22,31,.25),0 10px 28px rgba(220,22,31,.20);
  --display:'Saira',system-ui,sans-serif;--body:'Inter',system-ui,sans-serif;--mono:'JetBrains Mono',ui-monospace,monospace;
}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{margin:0;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:var(--body);font-size:16px;line-height:1.6}
h1,h2,h3,h4{margin:0;font-family:var(--display);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-.01em;line-height:1.05;text-transform:uppercase}
.wrap{max-width:1080px;margin:0 auto;padding:40px 24px}
.doc-h{border-left:4px solid var(--red);padding:4px 0 4px 16px;margin:48px 0 8px}
.doc-h h2{font-style:italic;font-size:24px}
.use{font-size:13.5px;color:var(--text-2);background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:10px 14px;margin:8px 0 18px}
.use b{color:var(--green-700)}.use .no{color:var(--red-700);font-weight:600}
.demo{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-lg);padding:24px;margin-bottom:8px}
.eyebrow{font-family:var(--body);font-weight:600;font-size:11px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--red);display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:8px}
.eyebrow::before{content:"";width:18px;height:2px;background:var(--red)}
.note{background:var(--amber-wash);border:1px solid var(--amber-300);border-left:4px solid var(--amber);border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:14px 16px;font-size:14px;margin:14px 0}

/* ===== SIGNATURES ===== */
.race-rule{height:14px;width:100%;background-color:#fff;background-image:linear-gradient(45deg,var(--ink) 25%,transparent 25%),linear-gradient(-45deg,var(--ink) 25%,transparent 25%),linear-gradient(45deg,transparent 75%,var(--ink) 75%),linear-gradient(-45deg,transparent 75%,var(--ink) 75%);background-size:14px 14px;background-position:0 0,0 7px,7px -7px,-7px 0;border-top:2px solid var(--red);border-bottom:2px solid var(--red)}
.hazard{height:6px;background:repeating-linear-gradient(45deg,var(--amber) 0 12px,var(--ink) 12px 24px)}

/* ===== BUTTONS ===== */
.btn{--bg:transparent;--fg:var(--text);--bd:transparent;font-family:var(--display);font-weight:700;font-style:italic;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.04em;font-size:14px;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:8px;cursor:pointer;padding:0 20px;height:48px;border-radius:var(--r-md);border:1.5px solid var(--bd);background:var(--bg);color:var(--fg);transition:transform .07s,background .15s,box-shadow .15s,border-color .15s}
.btn .ic{font-style:normal;font-weight:700}
.btn--filled{--bg:var(--red);--fg:#fff;--bd:var(--red);box-shadow:var(--e1)}.btn--filled:hover{--bg:var(--red-700);box-shadow:var(--glow-red)}
.btn--amber{--bg:var(--amber);--fg:#3a2600;--bd:var(--amber)}
.btn--ink{--bg:var(--ink);--fg:#fff;--bd:var(--ink)}
.btn--outline{--bg:transparent;--fg:var(--text);--bd:var(--line-strong)}
.btn--go{--bg:var(--green);--fg:#fff;--bd:var(--green)}

/* ===== ECO BADGE ===== */
.ecobadge{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:7px;font-weight:700;font-size:12px;color:var(--green-700);background:var(--green-wash);border:1px solid var(--green-line);border-radius:var(--r-pill);padding:5px 12px}

/* ===== PHOTO PLACEHOLDER (always label the exact shot) ===== */
.ph{position:relative;border-radius:var(--r-lg);overflow:hidden;border:1.5px dashed var(--line-strong);background:repeating-linear-gradient(45deg,#fafafb 0 10px,#f1f1f4 10px 20px);display:grid;place-items:center;text-align:center}
.ph--16x9{aspect-ratio:16/9}
.ph-in{padding:16px;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:5px;align-items:center}
.ph-cam{font-size:22px}.ph-kick{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.16em;color:var(--amber-600)}
.ph-desc{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-2);font-weight:500}.ph-spec{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;color:var(--text-3)}

/* ===== FORM FIELD ===== */
.field{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;margin-bottom:14px}
.field label{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.04em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--text-2)}
.field input,.field select{height:48px;background:#fff;border:1.5px solid var(--line-2);border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:0 14px;font-family:var(--body);font-size:15px;outline:none}
.field input:focus{border-color:var(--red)}

/* ===== TRUST BAR ===== */
.trustbar{background:var(--surface-3);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-lg);display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:16px;padding:24px}
.trustbar .item{text-align:center}
.trustbar .n{font-family:var(--display);font-style:italic;font-weight:800;font-size:20px}
.trustbar .l{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--text-2)}

/* ===== CONTENT CARD ===== */
.card{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-top:4px solid var(--red);border-radius:var(--r-lg);box-shadow:var(--e1);padding:24px}
.card h3{font-style:italic;font-size:19px;margin-bottom:8px}.card p{margin:0;color:var(--text-2);font-size:14.5px}

/* ===== FAQ ===== */
.faq details{background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--r-lg);box-shadow:var(--e1);margin-bottom:10px;overflow:hidden}
.faq summary{list-style:none;cursor:pointer;padding:16px 20px;font-family:var(--display);font-style:italic;font-weight:700;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;justify-content:space-between}
.faq summary .pm{color:var(--red)}.faq .ans{padding:0 20px 18px;color:var(--text-2);font-size:15px}
code{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12.5px;background:#fff;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:3px;padding:1px 5px}
.mini-footer{margin-top:48px;background:var(--ink);color:rgba(255,255,255,.72);border-radius:var(--r-lg);padding:24px}
.mini-footer .footer-logo{display:inline-flex;background:#fff;border-radius:var(--r-md);padding:8px 10px;width:230px;max-width:100%;line-height:0}
.mini-footer .footer-logo img{display:block;width:100%;height:auto}
.footer-links{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,minmax(0,1fr));gap:22px;margin-top:24px}
.footer-links h3{font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.12em;color:rgba(255,255,255,.48);margin:0 0 12px}
.footer-links a{display:block;color:rgba(255,255,255,.74);text-decoration:none;font-size:14px;margin:0 0 8px}
.footer-links a:hover{color:#fff}
@media(max-width:820px){.footer-links{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr))}}
@media(max-width:560px){.footer-links{grid-template-columns:1fr}.wrap{padding-left:16px;padding-right:16px}.demo[style*="grid-template-columns"]{grid-template-columns:1fr!important}.trustbar{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}}
@media(max-width:380px){.trustbar{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="wrap">
  <span class="eyebrow">Kiker's U-Pull-It</span>
  <h1 style="font-style:italic;font-size:34px;margin:8px 0 6px">Web Component Kit</h1>
  <p style="color:var(--text-2);max-width:62ch">This is a <b>parts bin, not a page layout.</b> Pick components to serve the flow defined in the page's UX brief — never reorder a page to fit these parts. Copy the <code>:root</code> token block and the component CSS you need into each page. Every page must still pass the <code>kikers-web-ux</code> brief gate before it's built.</p>

  <div class="note"><b>The rule:</b> using these components is NOT the same as designing the UX. The brief decides which parts appear, in what order, and why. If a part doesn't answer a real user question on that page, it doesn't go on the page.</div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Signatures</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> breaking between major zones or above the footer (race rule), or as a thin top accent on dialogs/cards (hazard). <span class="no">Don't</span> sprinkle — it's a rare flourish.</div>
  <div class="demo"><div class="race-rule"></div><div style="height:10px"></div><div class="hazard"></div></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Buttons</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Filled red</b> = the one primary action per view. <b>Amber</b> = high-energy primary on dark/red backgrounds. <b>Ink</b> = strong secondary. <b>Outline</b> = quiet tertiary. <b>Go (green)</b> = money/success only. <span class="no">Never</span> show two red primaries competing in one view.</div>
  <div class="demo" style="display:flex;gap:10px;flex-wrap:wrap">
    <button class="btn btn--filled"><span class="ic">⚡</span>Get My Offer</button>
    <button class="btn btn--amber">Call the Yard</button>
    <button class="btn btn--ink">Browse Inventory</button>
    <button class="btn btn--outline">Learn More</button>
    <button class="btn btn--go"><span class="ic">✓</span>Accept</button>
  </div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Eco badge</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> reinforcing responsible recycling — small, repeatable, droppable in hero tags, on vehicle cards, or as a full-width strip. It's a badge, not a section.</div>
  <div class="demo"><span class="ecobadge">♻ Recycled responsibly</span></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Photo placeholder</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> a real photo belongs there. ALWAYS state the exact shot, ratio, and orientation in the label so it doubles as a shot list. <span class="no">Don't</span> hand-draw representational SVG art — use real photos or commissioned/generated assets.</div>
  <div class="demo"><div class="ph ph--16x9"><div class="ph-in"><span class="ph-cam">📷</span><span class="ph-kick">PHOTO — WHAT GOES HERE</span><span class="ph-desc">Describe the exact shot (subject, setting, mood).</span><span class="ph-spec">16:9</span></div></div></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Form field</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use the fewest fields the job needs.</b> A cash-offer form needs vehicle + condition + phone, not a full profile. Extra fields are hurdles. Multiple form entry points ONLY where intent is high.</div>
  <div class="demo" style="max-width:420px">
    <div class="field"><label>Year, make &amp; model</label><input placeholder="2012 Honda Civic"></div>
    <div class="field"><label>Phone</label><input placeholder="(850) 000-0000"></div>
    <button class="btn btn--filled" style="width:100%"><span class="ic">⚡</span>Get My Cash Offer</button>
  </div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Trust bar</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> four (and only four) proof points reinforce the page's job. Swap the four to fit the page — a Sell page leads with speed/towing/paperwork; a parts page would lead with selection/organization/price.</div>
  <div class="demo"><div class="trustbar"><div class="item"><div class="n">Same-Day</div><div class="l">Pickup &amp; Cash</div></div><div class="item"><div class="n">Free</div><div class="l">Towing</div></div><div class="item"><div class="n">Handled</div><div class="l">Paperwork</div></div><div class="item"><div class="n">25 Years</div><div class="l">Family-Owned</div></div></div></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Content card</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> presenting parallel options/services. <span class="no">Don't</span> force three when the page only has two real ones — a filler third card is the #1 boilerplate tell.</div>
  <div class="demo" style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:16px"><div class="card"><h3>Cash for Cars</h3><p>Fair offer, free towing, same-day pickup.</p></div><div class="card"><h3>Pull Your Own Parts</h3><p>Bring tools, pull parts, pay at the counter.</p></div></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>FAQ (+ FAQPage schema)</h2></div>
  <div class="use"><b>Use when</b> the page answers real, repeated questions — great for users AND AI citation. The visible Q&amp;A must match the JSON-LD FAQPage 1:1, or Google ignores it.</div>
  <div class="demo"><div class="faq"><details open><summary>Do you buy cars that don't run? <span class="pm">+</span></summary><div class="ans">Yes — running or not, wrecked or junk.</div></details></div></div>

  <div class="doc-h"><h2>Also in the kit (CSS in the page files)</h2></div>
  <div class="use">Sticky nav + mobile drawer, utility strip (NAP), breadcrumb, dark hero (with labeled photo background), embedded form bands (ink/light), hours table with live today-highlight, custom service-area SVG map, footer with the values line, toast. Pull these from the existing page files; keep NAP, hours, phone, and schema identical across every page.</div>

  <p style="margin-top:40px;color:var(--text-3);font-size:13px">Kiker's U-Pull-It · web component kit · pair with the <code>kikers-web-ux</code> skill. Components serve the brief — the brief never serves the components.</p>

